@node "instructions" "-Some Brief Instructions For GOldNEST-"
@toc "main"
GOldNEST is a tool to edit .NES rom files. With GOldNEST you're able to alter the graphics in a
nes rom-image, an later save it to the same, or a new image.
From version 0.19 you may also change the integrated name (if present).
When changing names, I do not know if you should delete the unreadable characters at the end of
the name, I believe they are PC-end-of-line-cr chars, please leave them there!

You can save your palettes, they'll be saved in my own format: GOldNEST Palette (.GNP)
The .GNP extension is not required, but suitable in my opinion!

There's not much to say...You'll figure out the most yourself I believe!

A short description of the shortkeys follows...
-----------------------------------------------
Keys that works with/without Right-Amiga key pressed:
"+" skip to next block of graphics
"-" skip to previous block of graphics
"ESC" EXIT GOldNEST!

With Right-Amiga key pressed:
"O" open a new rom
"W" save over rom
"S" save rom as...
"L" Load a new palette
"Z" Save the current palette to a file!
"?" bring up the about information!

"P" To bring up the palette selector!
"E" expand the block window to display more graphics at once =)
"M" enables the marker in the rom graphics window. 

"G" open/close rom graphics window!

---

By disabling "Safe Edit Mode" from the Setting menu you will be able to edit more
nes-roms. But beware...You will also be able to edit the program-data, to put it
in another way: You can destroy your NES-Rom by drawing at the wrong places!
Make sure that you have backups and that you only redraw the things that really are graphics!

If you want to speed up the development, just write me a nice letter telling you like
this editor. If you have any suggestions for improvment, please tell me them.

GOldNEST now also takes a .NES rom image as a command line.

More instructions will be available in the future.
@endnode

@node "intro" "-A Brief Introduction To GOldNEST-
@toc "main"
@{i}
The Story
---------
It all started when I wanted to translate NES roms into Swedish. Therefore I joined 
"The Translators" and started to translate SMB-1 into swedish, and I was successfull!
After some hard work I finally changed some of the letters to swedish ones, and also
hacked the text in the romfile. The problem is that most of the NES roms do not use
standard ASCII-codes and that's a BIG problem if you want to translate roms. Therefore
I thought, why not create a NES tool for my favourite computer, Amiga. As you can see
I did, although there's much much more to be added and finished on this editor, it is
going to be the ultimate editor for any system (Maybe) !

My favourite emulator is CoolNESs by Fredrik Olsson (flubba@hem2.passagen.se), so I've
chosen a similar name for this editor: "GOldNEST"

GOldNEST is short for Good Old Nintendo Entertainment System Tool, so now you know...

@{ui}

@endnode

@node "installation" "-Installation-"
@toc "main"
From version 0.12 of GOldNEST there's an installer-script, just click on the
"GOldNEST.Install icon and you'll be guided thru the installation, very simple!

Tomas Amsrud helped me updating and fixing this script, thanks again Tomas!
@endnode

