@node "faq" "-Frequently Asked Questions-"
@toc "main"
Q: Why isn't the palette correct?
A: The NES graphics are built up in blocks of 8*8 pixels and they are always in 2 planes,
   the palette is never included in these blocks, it could be anywhere in the ROM.
   It's impossible to access the palette without some kind of emulation, therefore you will
   always have to set the palette by hand sorry :( 

Q: In my saved iff picture, my palette aren't exactly as I set it to!?
A: That's because iff.library lacks AGA support?, that's why you get values close to original values!

Q: Why are there bugs in GOldNEST?
A: Because, a guy called Lennart put them there! No really, every program has bugs.
   That's just the way it is.
   On the other hand I will remove bugs I find in GOldNEST in the future! =)

Q: Why is GOldNEST so d*mn slow?
A: GOldNEST is entirely written in C, and uses many system routines, which causes SlowNESs =)
   Some routines have been speeded up during the development though!

Q: My 16-colour-mcp-hires-pointer has the wrong colours!
A: Some modes just wont work properly with a hires 16 colour pointer, higher resolutions usually
   works, try different resolutions and see which one that fits you the best!
 
@endnode


@node "bugs" "-Bugs-"
@toc "main"
I believe there is a bug in the change name function but I'm not quite sure yet. Also another
thing when changing names, do NOT delete the unreadable characters at the end of the name, they
should be there! (I think!)

Always remember to save all important work before running GOldNEST and make sure you backup
your roms first!

Also please, if you have a graphics-board, tell me if this program works on such a screen.

I know there are more bugs in this program, but I need you to find them for me.
PLEASE! If you find any bugs please report them to @{"me" link "me" 0}.
@endnode

@node "history" "-History-"
@toc "main"
The (so far) history of GOldNEST:

0.42: (08-Jan-99)
GOldNEST is now a Seasons project. Still written by me Lennart, though.
You are now able to load (all?) roms by untagging the new menu-option: "Safe Edit Mode".
Newicons made by Tomas "AER" Amsrud Added!
Now GOldNEST uses Nintendo.Font, special thanks to the A/NES crew for the font!

0.40: (10-Oct-98)
GOldNEST is now mailware, support me by sending me a mail!
Added Save Iff Support! (Requires iff.library)
Added Save CFG On Exit & Save Config Options. (Suggested by Tomas Amsrud!)

0.35: (29-Jul-98)
Loading/Saving Palettes! Send me your favourite palettes and I'll Include them!
Fixed some enforcer hits, there's still some of them left though...

0.30: (22-Jul-98)
Better palette support with sliders and palette gadgets! (RAmiga+P)
Bugfixes to the block-palette selector and code.
Bugfixes to the menuhandler, works better than expected! =)

0.20: (31-May-98)
Removed GOldNEST start script, GOldNEST can be run directly from it's icon now =)
Added a menu option to enable marker for blocks =)
Fixed the romnamelength bug? (Not sure if I really did though, please report!)

0.19: (08-May-98)
Now you can change the integrated name in the rom file from GOldNEST! (Buggy)
Removed NES-manager from the GOldNEST archive.
Reorganized the code a little.

0.18: (06-May-98)
More prefs are now saved, window positions and window size!
Scrollbar for graphics, now you can't draw outside memory anymore =)
Some bugfixes, hopefully no more crashed when changing window-size =)

0.17: (01-May-98)
Added high speed bitmap mode for ECS/AGA screens!
Use + and - without pressing right amiga keys.
Fixed some bugs (1 enforcer hit that caused another enforcer hit removed!)

0.16: (22-Apr-98)
Heavily improved the filename-handling, now it should work better! (I hope)
Enabled "Save Rom as" in the menu, so you don't have to save over you old ROMs =) 

0.15: (20-Apr-98)
Major improvements! You are now capable of editing graphics, and also writing them to
the ROM. So get started making your own graphics NOW, and make sure you've backed up
your ROM-images first!
Also some fixes to the GUI and other great features!

0.14: (18-Apr-98)
Great improvment to the message handler (for windows etc.)!
GOldNEST now takes command line. (Suggested by Tomas Amsrud)
Config is now saved to ENVARC: and ENV:

0.13: (07-Apr-98)
Now you can browse through the graphics in the rom =)
First palette support (I promise you all a better one in the future!)
Added SmalMWB, Smal and Normal Icons by Tomas Amsrud (gdwarf@applausenett.no)!
Install script updated (also by Tomas Amsrud)
Thanks for your support Tomas =)

0.12: (28-Mar-98)
Added Installer script.
Now graphic window display the filename of the loaded ROM. (Suggested by Tomas Amsrud!)
Added MWB icons made by Tomas Amsrud!

0.11: (26-Mar-98)
Now the correct graphics offset is calculated. (No more corrupted graphics)
GOldNEST also shows more colors now, (The last one showed only 3 colors due to a bug.)
Also some minor changes to the source.

0.10: (25-Mar-98)
First Public Release.

@endnode
